{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-readme-js","path":"/rabbiabram/awesome-fortran/readme/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"997aa160-a48d-5068-8907-163a56c98a3e","html":"<h1 id=\"awesome-fortran-awesome-build-status\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#awesome-fortran-awesome-build-status\" aria-label=\"awesome fortran awesome build status permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Awesome Fortran <a href=\"https://github.com/sindresorhus/awesome\"><img src=\"https://cdn.rawgit.com/sindresorhus/awesome/d7305f38d29fed78fa85652e3a63e154dd8e8829/media/badge.svg\" alt=\"Awesome\"></a> <a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/rabbiabram/awesome-fortran\"><img src=\"https://api.travis-ci.org/rabbiabram/awesome-fortran.svg?branch=master\" alt=\"Build Status\"></a></h1>\n<p>A curated list of awesome Fortran frameworks, libraries and software. Inspired by <a href=\"https://github.com/Wolg/awesome-swift\">awesome-swift</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Wolg/awesome-swift\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">5.2k</span></span></a> by @Wolg.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#awesome-fortran\">Awesome Fortran</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#functional-libraries\">Functional Libraries</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#graphics-libraries\">Graphics Libraries</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#math-libs\">Math libs</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#json-manipulation\">JSON Manipulation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#xml-manipulation\">XML Manipulation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#date-and-time-manipulation\">Date and time manipulation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#testing\">Testing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#encoding-decoding\">Encoding-Decoding</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#portability-enabling\">Portability enabling</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#command-line-parsing\">Command-Line parsing</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#compiling-and-building\">Compiling and building</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#preprocessor\">Preprocessor</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#automatic-documentation\">Automatic documentation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#computational-fluid-dynamics\">Computational Fluid Dynamics</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#docker\">Docker</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#web\">Web</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#resources\">Resources</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#fortran-websites\">Fortran Websites</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#fortran-videos\">Fortran Videos</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><a href=\"#other-awesome-lists\">Other Awesome Lists</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#contributing\">Contributing</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"functional-libraries\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#functional-libraries\" aria-label=\"functional libraries permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Functional Libraries</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wavebitscientific/functional-fortran\">Functional Fortran</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/wavebitscientific/functional-fortran\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">317</span></span></a> - Functional programming for modern Fortran.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"graphics-libraries\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#graphics-libraries\" aria-label=\"graphics libraries permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Graphics Libraries</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for graphing, graphics, and GUIs</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.mps.mpg.de/dislin/\">DISLIN</a> - a high-level graphing and user-interface library.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://math.nist.gov/f90gl/\">f90gl</a> - public domain implementation of the official NIST Fortran 90 bindings for OpenGL.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www-stone.ch.cam.ac.uk/pub/f03gl/index.xhtml\">F03GL</a> - a Fortran 2003 interface to the OpenGL library, along with the GLU and GLUT toolkits.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vmagnin/gtk-fortran/wiki\">gtk-fortran</a> - a cross-platform library to build Graphical User Interfaces (GUI) using <a href=\"https://www.gtk.org/\">GTK+</a>.  Very useful when combined with the <a href=\"https://glade.gnome.org/\">Glade</a> RAD tool.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.astro.caltech.edu/~tjp/pgplot/\">PGPLOT</a> - cross-platform scientific graphing library.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/VTKFortran\">VTKFortran</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/VTKFortran\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">92</span></span></a> - Pure Fortran (2003+) library to write and read data conforming the VTK standard.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"math-libs\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#math-libs\" aria-label=\"math libs permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Math Libs</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for calculating and other mathematical operations.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.netlib.org/blas/\">BLAS</a> - application programming interface standard for publishing libraries to perform basic linear algebra operations such as vector and matrix multiplication.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://cernlib.web.cern.ch/cernlib/\">CERNLIB</a> - The CERN Program Library is a large collection of general purpose libraries and modules maintained and offered in both source and object code form on the CERN central computers</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.netlib.org/eispack/\">EISPACK</a> - a software library for numerical computation of eigenvalues and eigenvectors of matrices, written in FORTRAN</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.lrz.de/services/software/mathematik/gsl/fortran/index.html\">FGSL</a> - portable, object-based Fortran interface to the <a href=\"https://www.lrz.de/services/software/mathematik/gsl/\">GNU scientific library</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.imsl.com/products/imsl-fortran-libraries\">IMSL</a> - The IMSL Fortran Numerical Library is the standard for high performance computing commercial mathematics and statistics libraries</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.ssisc.org/lis/index.en.html\">Lis</a> - a Library of Iterative Solvers for Linear Systems</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.nag.co.uk/content/nag-library-fortran\">NAG Fortran Library</a> - Produced by experts for use in a variety of applications, the NAG Fortran Library has a global reputation for its excellence and, with hundreds of fully documented and tested routines, is the largest collection of mathematical and statistical algorithms available</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Unidata/netcdf-fortran\">netCDF</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/Unidata/netcdf-fortran\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">141</span></span></a> - a set of software libraries and self-describing, machine-independent data formats that support the creation, access, and sharing of array-oriented scientific data.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/xianyi/OpenBLAS\">OpenBLAS</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/xianyi/OpenBLAS\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.9k</span></span></a> - one of the fastest open source BLAS libraries available.  Almost as fast as Intel MKL.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"json-manipulation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#json-manipulation\" aria-label=\"json manipulation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>JSON Manipulation</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for JSON data manipulating with Fortran language.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/josephalevin/fson\">FSON</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/josephalevin/fson\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">57</span></span></a> - Fortran 95 JSON Parser.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jacobwilliams/json-fortran\">json-fortran</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jacobwilliams/json-fortran\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">222</span></span></a> - A Fortran 2008 JSON API.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"xml-manipulation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#xml-manipulation\" aria-label=\"xml manipulation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>XML Manipulation</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for XML data manipulating with Fortran language.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/andreww/fox\">fox</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/andreww/fox\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">47</span></span></a> - Fortran XML library</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/xml-fortran/\">xml-fortran</a> - an all-Fortran solution for reading and writing XML files.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"date-and-time-manipulation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#date-and-time-manipulation\" aria-label=\"date and time manipulation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Date and time manipulation</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for date and time manipulation with Fortran language.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/wavebitscientific/datetime-fortran\">datetime-fortran</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/wavebitscientific/datetime-fortran\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">94</span></span></a> - A Fortran 2003 date and time manipulation library, modeled after Python's datetime library.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"testing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#testing\" aria-label=\"testing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Testing</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for testing codebases and generating test data.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/fortranxunit/\">FRUIT</a> - FORTRAN Unit Test Framework, written in FORTRAN 95</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://flibs.sourceforge.net/ftnunit.html\">Ftunit</a> - Fortran unit testing framework by Arjen Markus</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://sourceforge.net/projects/pfunit/\">pFUnit</a> - Unit testing framework for Fortran with MPI extensions by developers from NASA and NGC TASC.  Uses parallel codes and object-oriented design.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://gitlab.com/everythingfunctional/vegetables\">Vegetables</a> - For a healthier code base, eat your vegetables</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"encoding-decoding\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#encoding-decoding\" aria-label=\"encoding decoding permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Encoding-Decoding</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for encoding and decoding data with Fortran language.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/BeFoR64\">BeFoR64</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/BeFoR64\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">16</span></span></a> - Base64 encoding/decoding library for FoRtran poor men. A KISS library for base64 encoding/decoding for modern (2003+) Fortran projects.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"portability-enabling\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#portability-enabling\" aria-label=\"portability enabling permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Portability enabling</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for enabling codes portability.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/PENF\">PENF</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/PENF\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">31</span></span></a> - Pure Fortran (2003+) library for ensuring codes portability.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"command-line-parsing\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#command-line-parsing\" aria-label=\"command line parsing permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Command-Line parsing</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for parsing command-line and building user interfaces.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/FLAP\">FLAP</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/FLAP\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">110</span></span></a> - Fortran command Line Arguments Parser for poor men. A KISS library for building easily nice Command Line Interfaces (CLI) for modern (2003+) Fortran projects.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cngilbreth/optionsf90\">options.f90</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cngilbreth/optionsf90\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">10</span></span></a> - Options &#x26; input processing for modern Fortran.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"compiling-and-building\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#compiling-and-building\" aria-label=\"compiling and building permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Compiling and building</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for compiling and building Fortran projects.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/FoBiS\">FoBiS</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/FoBiS\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">114</span></span></a> - Fortran Building System for poor men. A KISS tool for automatic building modern Fortran projects.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"preprocessor\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#preprocessor\" aria-label=\"preprocessor permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Preprocessor</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for conditional-compilation, macros for code simplification, and inclusion of additional source files, templating systems.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"http://blockit.sourceforge.net/\">Blockit/PyF95++</a> - A fairly simple Python framework used to block parse your code (or any text file) into nested blocks. The BlockIt framework has already been used to create a templating capability for the Fortran 95/2003 language along with some language extensions.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/PreForM\">PreForM</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/PreForM\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">23</span></span></a> - Preprocessor for Fortran poor Men.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"automatic-documentation\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#automatic-documentation\" aria-label=\"automatic documentation permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Automatic documentation</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for building documentation.</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/cmacmackin/ford\">FORD</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/cmacmackin/ford\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">27</span></span></a> - An automatic documentation generator for modern Fortran programs.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"computational-fluid-dynamics\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#computational-fluid-dynamics\" aria-label=\"computational fluid dynamics permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Computational Fluid Dynamics</h2>\n<p><em>Libraries for CFD computations</em></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/szaghi/OFF/tree/testing\">OFF</a> - Open source Finite volume Fluid dynamics code.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"docker\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#docker\" aria-label=\"docker permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Docker</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://hub.docker.com/r/baekjoon/onlinejudge-fortran/\">Unoficial Image</a> - docker image provided by @baekjoon</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"web\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#web\" aria-label=\"web permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Web</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/mapmeld/fortran-machine\">Fortran Machine</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/mapmeld/fortran-machine\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">675</span></span></a> - An MVC web stack written in Fortran 90</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"resources\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#resources\" aria-label=\"resources permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Resources</h1>\n<p>Various resources, such as books, websites and articles, for improving your Fortran development skills and knowledge.</p>\n<h2 id=\"fortran-websites\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#fortran-websites\" aria-label=\"fortran websites permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 